claim: In the 1960's, George Tuska worked on Iron Man comics.
premise_source_doc_sentence: George Tuska  (  April 26 , 1916 -- October 16 , 2009  )  , who early in his career used a variety of pen names including Carl Larson , was an American comic book and newspaper comic strip artist best known for his 1940s work on various Captain Marvel titles and the crime fiction series Crime Does Not Pay , for and his 1960s work illustrating Iron Man and other Marvel Comics characters .
